.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This script is one of the \fBoctopus\fR utilities.
.PP
This script runs the Octopus testsuite.
.PP
The man pages of Octopus and of the auxiliary Octopus
sub-programs (oct-something) are not intended to contain the
documentation of the programs, but only their basic
description. For where to find more documentation, see the
\&\*(L"\s-1SEE\s0 \s-1ALSO\s0\*(R" section below.
.IP "\fB\-h\fR" 4
.IX Item "-h"
Prints out a short help message.
.IP "\fB\-n\fR" 4
.IX Item "-n"
Run in dry mode (show what would be executed).
.IP "\fB\-g\fR \fI\s-1LIST\s0\fR" 4
.IX Item "-g LIST"
Comma-separated list of test groups to run. If not present, all tests
are run.
.IP "\fB\-q\fR" 4
.IX Item "-q"
Query testfiles belonging to groups given with \fB\-g\fR option. No tests
are performed.
.IP "\fB\-d\fR \fI\s-1DIR\s0\fR" 4
.IX Item "-d DIR"
Directory where to look for the testsuite.
.IP "\fB\-l\fR" 4
.IX Item "-l"
Local run.
.IP "\fB\-e\fR \fI\s-1SUFFIX\s0\fR" 4
.IX Item "-e SUFFIX"
Suffix to append to the Octopus executable file name.
.IP "\fB\-p\fR \fI\s-1PREFIX\s0\fR" 4
.IX Item "-p PREFIX"
Installation prefix [default: /usr].
.IP "\fB\-w\fR" 4
.IX Item "-w"
Run without \s-1MPI\s0 (parallel) tests.
.IP "\fB\-c\fR" 4
.IX Item "-c"
Clean up all .log files after the testuite run.
.IP "\fB\-m\fR \fI\s-1ADDRESS\s0\fR" 4
.IX Item "-m ADDRESS"
Mail report to address.
